    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1928"/>, p. 327, n. <citedRange>7</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.81</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#paribeni1959"/>, n. <citedRange>60</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>17.794</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1976"/><citedRange/></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>26.1832</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl>again <ptr target="#gasperini2008"/>, pp. <citedRange>119-123</citedRange></bibl>
;                    <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>182-183, 196 footnote 140</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>38.1896</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>017500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65474"><name nymRef="#Πρατομήδης"><supplied reason="lost">Πρατο</supplied>μήδης</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65392"><name nymRef="#Πόλυμνις" type="patronymic"><supplied reason="lost">Πολύ</supplied>μνιος</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλ</supplied>λ<unclear>ω</unclear>ν<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied></name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Pratomedes fils de Polymnis <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré</supplied> à Apollon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Pratomedes son of Polymnis <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated</supplied> to Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Pratomedes figlio di Polymnis <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato</supplied> ad Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>In the debated question of the function and date of the whole monument (fountain, exedra?), L. Gasperini (<bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1976"/></bibl>) gives epigraphical arguments
                    for Oliverio's dating towards the end of IV BC. So also <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>182-183</citedRange></bibl> with bibliography.</p>
	<p>The colour picture (courtesy H. Walda, IRCyr project) was taken in 2008. Sitting at right of the exedra is Joyce M. Reynolds during her last visit to Cyrene.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
